12.  RELATED DATA SETS

NCDS supports several other data sets online containing ozone measurements.
The GRIDTOMS daily and monthly data for the period October 1978 - December
1989 are available, and are accessible through the Data Applications
Subsystem of NCDS by specifying the following CDF names:

          GRIDTOMS_XXXX *
          GRIDTOMS_MONTHLY

Also available are ozone monthly averages and hour-monthly averages derived
from the AVHRR, MIR, VAS, and VISSR instruments onboard the NOAA, METEOSAT,
GOES, and GMS series of satellites respectively, for the International
Satellite Cloud Climatology Project (ISCCP-C2). These data can be accessed
within the NCDS Data Application Subsystem by specifying the following CDF
names:

          ISCCP-C2_MONTHLY
          ISCCP-C2_MONTHLY

* where XXXX is the year of interest in the range 1978 - 1989

The SAGE I and SAGE II data, from the AEM-2 satellite and the Earth
Radiation Budget satellite (ERBS) respectively, contains ozone profile
data.  The SAGE I data covers the period Feb 21, 1979 through Nov 18, 1981,
and the SAGE II data covers the period Oct 21, 1984 through the present.
These data are available on magnetic tape from NCDS, and through the Data
Access Subsystem of NCDS.  The SAGE II data will also be available on the
GEDEX CD-ROM, scheduled for release in early spring 1992.


